<m0>veryone's so preoccupied with AIDS these days that we seem to have forgotten all about the prospect that <m0>used <m0>to terrify couples: <m0>What if you get pregnant?<m0> <ep>
   Whether you've been seeing each other two weeks, two months or two years, a pregnancy can smother a courtship. It can lead to your relationship's destruction (--) or it can help bring you closer.<ep>
   ``Lynn,'' a 40-year-old senior financial analyst, had been seeing her boyfriend for two months when she got pregnant. When she told him, she got another shock. He told her he had a wife in the Dominican Republic.<ep>
   ``My position was, `I'm too old for this bull,' '' she says. ``I had a good job, I had saved up money. I basically said I'd do it without him. So I got rid of him. I said I didn't want anything to do with him.''<ep>
   <m2><ql>
